understand the present situation in Hong Kong.

142
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:45,250
Or they understand it,

143
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:53,660
but they just turn a blind eye to the critical
situation.

144
00:08:53,660 --> 00:08:57,890
Or maybe it's something that the Chinese government
wants to do

145
00:08:57,890 --> 00:09:05,430
because after pausing, or actually after the
1st of October,

146
00:09:05,430 --> 00:09:10,430
the National Day, they can do anything they
want, they think.

147
00:09:10,430 --> 00:09:15,190
And probably they will use even more high
handed method

148
00:09:15,190 --> 00:09:19,920
to suppress or to press Hong Kong people.

149
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:23,450
So this is a part of their strategy.

150
00:09:23,450 --> 00:09:25,149
What do you think legislators like yourself

151
00:09:25,149 --> 00:09:28,450
can do to challenge Beijing's will in Hong
Kong?

152
00:09:28,450 --> 00:09:32,750
Unfortunately we are the minority

153
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:37,180
under the present political situation.

154
00:09:37,180 --> 00:09:39,500
It might be very difficult for us

155
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:46,019
to get all these motions or even these motions
to be passed.

156
00:09:46,019 --> 00:09:49,079
But if the government,

157
00:09:49,079 --> 00:09:51,080
or if Mrs. Carrie Lam,

158
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:54,740
once you pass this very powerful law, for
example,

159
00:09:54,740 --> 00:10:05,310
like the anti mask law, based on emergency
regulations ordinance,

160
00:10:05,310 --> 00:10:09,560
I think this will have a very longterm

161
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:14,250
and negative effect on Hong Kong.

162
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:17,350
And it will definitely affect Hong Kong's
economy

163
00:10:17,350 --> 00:10:20,980
and international reputation.

164
00:10:20,980 --> 00:10:27,300
So I really want to remind her

165
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:36,320
that though it may have some short term effect,

166
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:41,209
