168
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:44,970
what would they do?

169
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:45,970
What kind of powers

170
00:10:45,970 --> 00:10:47,480
would they give Carrie Lam?

171
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:51,410
First of all, these emergency regulation ordinance

172
00:10:51,410 --> 00:10:54,720
is a very powerful ordinance because the name,

173
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:57,660
you can tell from name,

174
00:10:57,660 --> 00:11:01,639
and Mrs. Carrie Lam can avoid to take the
bill

175
00:11:01,639 --> 00:11:05,029
to the legislature for legislature's scrutiny.

176
00:11:05,029 --> 00:11:11,220
So she together with the executive council
can pass a law,

177
00:11:11,220 --> 00:11:16,110
which is even inconsistent with the present
ordinances in Hong Kong.

178
00:11:16,110 --> 00:11:18,170
For example, like the Bill of Rights.

179
00:11:18,170 --> 00:11:23,230
So it's very easy for her to take away our
freedoms,

180
00:11:23,230 --> 00:11:29,339
our civil rights without any scrutiny of legislature.

181
00:11:29,339 --> 00:11:31,209
So it's a very, very dangerous,

182
00:11:31,209 --> 00:11:33,290
but at the same time a very powerful law.

183
00:11:33,290 --> 00:11:35,730
So it seems like there's some kind of shady
things

184
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:38,120
being done with basic law.

185
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:40,269
Yes, yes.

186
00:11:40,269 --> 00:11:41,760
And at the same time,

187
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:46,279
it's very difficult for legislators to voice

188
00:11:46,279 --> 00:11:54,339
or even to interrupt the only value left probably,

