for participating in the 2014 umbrella movement

196
00:12:21,579 --> 00:12:24,389
and given a suspended prison sentence.

197
00:12:24,389 --> 00:12:27,970
What are these protesters facing after arrest?

198
00:12:27,970 --> 00:12:34,339
First of all, of course is the pressure.

199
00:12:34,339 --> 00:12:37,899
If they got arrested, and they've got bail,

200
00:12:37,899 --> 00:12:40,720
of course they need to follow the bail terms,

201
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:43,490
no matter it is a court bail, or a police
bail.

202
00:12:43,490 --> 00:12:46,510
Secondly, they may be charged.

203
00:12:46,510 --> 00:12:50,720
The prosecution may lay charges against them
anytime,

204
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:59,050
and whether this situation will affect their
decision in the future,

205
00:12:59,050 --> 00:13:00,310
I don't know.

206
00:13:00,310 --> 00:13:02,589
But obviously for example, like for me,

207
00:13:02,589 --> 00:13:06,389
I've been arrested for three times and they
charged me

208
00:13:06,389 --> 00:13:16,079
at the very last occasion, with two very,
very unusual charges.

209
00:13:16,079 --> 00:13:21,390
One is incite people to commit a public nuisance.

210
00:13:21,390 --> 00:13:26,160
And the second one is incite others to incite
public nuisance.

211
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:27,410
Exactly.

212
00:13:27,410 --> 00:13:28,649
Exactly.

213
00:13:28,649 --> 00:13:29,899
Exactly.

214
00:13:29,899 --> 00:13:34,829
That's the reason why I need to name my two
counts of charges

215
00:13:34,829 --> 00:13:38,410
because it's not usual.

216
00:13:38,410 --> 00:13:40,871
And in fact, at that moment you can see that
in Hong Kong

217
00:13:40,871 --> 00:13:46,519
we have other charges that is more normal
and usual

218
00:13:46,519 --> 00:13:49,110
that can be used by the prosecution.

219
00:13:49,110 --> 00:13:54,980
But by charging us with, we call it a [inaudible]
offenses.

220
00:13:54,980 --> 00:13:58,449
That means aiding and abetting or inciting.

221
00:13:58,449 --> 00:14:01,630
This kind we call it [inaudible] offenses.

222
00:14:01,630 --> 00:14:05,830
The maximum penalty of these offenses is seven
years,

223
00:14:05,830 --> 00:14:11,430
so they can immediately escalate the maximum
penalty of our charges.

224
00:14:11,430 --> 00:14:13,400
So they make sure that we are going to face

225
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:17,360
the most serious charges that they can handle,

226
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:19,540
or at least they can try to prove.

227
00:14:19,540 --> 00:14:22,130
So that's our situation.

228
00:14:22,130 --> 00:14:27,120
And of course from 2014 until now,

229
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:31,690
we have only gone through the first level
of the court.

230
00:14:31,690 --> 00:14:34,490
So we have our case,

231
00:14:34,490 --> 00:14:40,089
it has been handled by the district court

232
00:14:40,089 --> 00:14:43,959
and now we are waiting for a court of appeal,

233
00:14:43,959 --> 00:14:46,079
and probably will go to the court of final
appeal.

234
00:14:46,079 --> 00:14:50,120
So the whole process may take three to four
years to finish.

235
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:54,970
And so, I can only tell those who are being
arrested,

236
00:14:54,970 --> 00:14:59,579
please do seek your legal advice.

237
00:14:59,579 --> 00:15:05,470
But at the same time, as a legislator with
a legal background,

238
00:15:05,470 --> 00:15:12,240
I would tell them that think twice before
they act.

239
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:15,470
Because I think most of them are prepared

240
00:15:15,470 --> 00:15:18,420
or at least prepared in a sense that they
understand

241
00:15:18,420 --> 00:15:20,430
the possibility of being charged.

242
00:15:20,430 --> 00:15:23,980
But still you may need to face them

243
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:26,550
and you may need to face them for a very long
time.

244
00:15:26,550 --> 00:15:32,949
So I still believe that people should think
twice before they act.

245
00:15:32,949 --> 00:15:37,370
So when you say that, should they not be protesting?

246
00:15:37,370 --> 00:15:39,839
Or how can they balance this fight

247
00:15:39,839 --> 00:15:44,050
that the protestors believe was staying safe?

248
00:15:44,050 --> 00:15:49,230
As far as I understand, some or most of the
protesters

249
00:15:49,230 --> 00:15:51,900
do understand that they are participating

250
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:56,300
in different kinds of activities.

251
00:15:56,300 --> 00:16:00,040
And all these activities, some of them may
lead to

252
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:06,870
various potential legal charges or criminal
charges

253
00:16:06,870 --> 00:16:14,930
that may affect their future.

254
00:16:14,930 --> 00:16:19,370
The only thing that I really want to tell
them is to think twice

255
00:16:19,370 --> 00:16:25,690
because that is something that not only will
